1. Installed Node.js (v20.16.0) and npm on my machine.
2. Attempted to install Sass v3.7.4 as instructed, but it is not available in the npm registry.
3. Installed the latest stable version of Sass instead using:
   npm install sass
4. Verified the installation with:
   npx sass --version
5. Sass was successfully installed and ready for use.
